# Example of how to mark secrets and configs in Choreo
# This file shows which values should be secrets vs plain configs

## SECRETS (sensitive data - add these as secrets in Choreo):
# - DB_PASSWORD
# - GEMINI_API_KEY  
# - GOOGLE_VISION_API_KEY
# - ASGARDEO_CLIENT_SECRET
# - JWT_SECRET
# - REDIS_PASSWORD (if using Redis)

## CONFIGS (non-sensitive - add as plain environment variables):
# - DB_HOST
# - DB_PORT
# - DB_USERNAME
# - DB_NAME
# - ASGARDEO_BASE_URL
# - ASGARDEO_CLIENT_ID
# - ASGARDEO_REDIRECT_URI
# - FRONTEND_URL
# - BACKEND_URL
# - ENVIRONMENT

# The Config.toml.choreo file already uses ${env:VARIABLE_NAME} syntax
# which will automatically pull from Choreo's environment variables